What are we doing?

259
00:11:57,309 --> 00:11:59,109
What are they doing for real?

260
00:12:00,039 --> 00:12:01,579
Before the date.

261
00:12:02,679 --> 00:12:04,478
- Cute.
- How adorable.

262
00:12:04,479 --> 00:12:05,519
Seriously.

263
00:12:06,249 --> 00:12:07,988
- That's youth.
- They're off.

264
00:12:07,989 --> 00:12:09,419
Here they go.

265
00:12:12,589 --> 00:12:15,228
(Girls' 1st-come 1st-served Date, Park Si Woo and Yoon Hoo)

266
00:12:15,229 --> 00:12:17,929
Si Woo chose Yoon Hoo in the First Impression Selection,

267
00:12:18,029 --> 00:12:21,469
while Yoon Hoo wants to get to know Si Woo better.

268
00:12:21,899 --> 00:12:23,728
Are you the type to get cold easily?

269
00:12:23,729 --> 00:12:25,068
No, not really.

270
00:12:25,069 --> 00:12:26,499
Not that much.

271
00:12:27,339 --> 00:12:29,369
- Let me.
- Thank you.

272
00:12:30,069 --> 00:12:31,439
- Thank you.
- Get in.

273
00:12:32,439 --> 00:12:34,309
He opened the door for her.

274
00:12:35,249 --> 00:12:37,678
- What?
- He opened the door for her.

275
00:12:37,679 --> 00:12:40,048
Earlier, he didn't open it for Yu Bin.

276
00:12:40,049 --> 00:12:41,848
- Yoon Hoo didn't open...
- Wait.

277
00:12:41,849 --> 00:12:43,769
- the door for Yu Bin.
- Isn't Yoon Hoo driving?

278
00:12:44,589 --> 00:12:46,259
Get in first.

279
00:12:47,089 --> 00:12:50,429
(Yoon Hoo told Yu Bin to get in and didn't open the door for her.)

280
00:12:50,829 --> 00:12:53,398
- He didn't open it for Yu Bin.
- No, he didn't.

281
00:12:53,399 --> 00:12:56,298
But during the date with Yu Bin, it was too narrow...

282
00:12:56,299 --> 00:12:58,668
- for Yoon Hoo to open it for her.
- How sharp.

283
00:12:58,669 --> 00:13:00,938
Nonsense, there was more than enough space.

284
00:13:00,939 --> 00:13:04,209
This lady keeps driving a wedge between us.

285
00:13:04,309 --> 00:13:06,739
Because of a door.

286
00:13:06,979 --> 00:13:08,909
But that just now was a bit...

287
00:13:09,049 --> 00:13:11,418
- You're right.
- He's very proactive.

288
00:13:11,419 --> 00:13:12,779
(He can't cover for him.)

289
00:13:13,979 --> 00:13:17,249
(Their first date finally begins.)

290
00:13:21,189 --> 00:13:22,359
Oh, also...

291
00:13:25,799 --> 00:13:27,599
My coat almost burned just now.

292
00:13:28,329 --> 00:13:30,068
- I brought this.
- Thank you.

293
00:13:30,069 --> 00:13:33,038
I already have two, but I'll be richer with this.

294
00:13:33,039 --> 00:13:34,069
Right.

295
00:13:34,169 --> 00:13:35,969
- Be a millionaire.
- Thanks.

296
00:13:37,069 --> 00:13:39,179
- Let me know if you need one.
- Well, I...

297
00:13:39,409 --> 00:13:40,639
I won't give you one, then.

298
00:13:41,779 --> 00:13:45,649
(One hand warmer changes the mood.)

299
00:13:45,949 --> 00:13:47,789
Do you think you changed your mind...

300
00:13:49,049 --> 00:13:50,189
from the first day?

301
00:13:50,589 --> 00:13:52,959
A little, I guess.

302
00:13:53,159 --> 00:13:55,329
But my interest...

303
00:13:55,759 --> 00:13:57,659
I'm sure you already know...

304
00:13:58,299 --> 00:14:00,768
I'll be straightforward.

305
00:14:00,769 --> 00:14:02,769
The two people I was most curious about...

306
00:14:03,269 --> 00:14:06,169
were Si Woo and Yu Bin.

307
00:14:09,869 --> 00:14:11,708
He made his first move.

308
00:14:11,709 --> 00:14:12,779
(That's my boy.)

309
00:14:13,779 --> 00:14:15,939
Why didn't you pick me for the First Impression, then?

310
00:14:16,649 --> 00:14:17,779
Well, that was...

311
00:14:19,049 --> 00:14:20,378
I sent it to you.

312
00:14:20,379 --> 00:14:22,189
(2 blows in a row)

313
00:14:22,689 --> 00:14:24,118
She came in out of nowhere.

314
00:14:24,119 --> 00:14:26,989
I literally never saw it coming.

315
00:14:28,159 --> 00:14:30,729
I thought you weren't interested at all.

316
00:14:32,199 --> 00:14:34,028
What made you feel that way?

317
00:14:34,029 --> 00:14:37,429
I'm sorry for saying this, but you looked like an ice queen.

318
00:14:37,939 --> 00:14:39,069
Ice queen.

319
00:14:39,599 --> 00:14:40,969
That's still a queen.

320
00:14:41,509 --> 00:14:42,809
That's good.

321
00:14:43,509 --> 00:14:45,439
And you looked...

322
00:14:46,979 --> 00:14:48,579
- Well, you're beautiful.
- Okay.

323
00:14:49,909 --> 00:14:52,679
And your skin is...

324
00:14:53,779 --> 00:14:55,889
as white as snow.

325
00:14:56,549 --> 00:14:57,888
(Hoo never stops flirting.)

326
00:14:57,889 --> 00:15:01,628
Didn't he continuously told Yu Bin she was beautiful?

327
00:15:01,629 --> 00:15:02,928
- Hold on.
- Hoo is...

328
00:15:02,929 --> 00:15:04,399
What is this?

329
00:15:05,129 --> 00:15:06,228
What is he doing?

330
00:15:06,229 --> 00:15:08,428
- Min Soo, explain.
- What's going on?

331
00:15:08,429 --> 00:15:09,998
He's committing to the current date.

332
00:15:09,999 --> 00:15:11,469
Stay out of this!

333
00:15:11,639 --> 00:15:12,868
Explain.

334
00:15:12,869 --> 00:15:14,808
- That's...
- He's only calling...

335
00:15:14,809 --> 00:15:17,539
a beautiful girl beautiful. Should he call her ugly?

336
00:15:17,979 --> 00:15:19,438
I'll keep an eye on him,

337
00:15:19,439 --> 00:15:22,248
but I'm starting to feel offended.

338
00:15:22,249 --> 00:15:23,478
When he was with Yu Bin...

339
00:15:23,479 --> 00:15:25,578
He's put on the spot.

340
00:15:25,579 --> 00:15:26,919
I can't look that way.

341
00:15:27,319 --> 00:15:28,348
Gosh.

342
00:15:28,349 --> 00:15:29,549
(He's too afraid.)

343
00:15:29,889 --> 00:15:31,759
But please don't be upset.

344
00:15:31,859 --> 00:15:33,088
I really want to get to know you.

345
00:15:33,089 --> 00:15:35,089
I even wrote you that letter yesterday.

346
00:15:36,589 --> 00:15:38,729
Oh, he told her!

347
00:15:39,499 --> 00:15:41,328
- Letter?
- She thought it was Hee Dong's.

348
00:15:41,329 --> 00:15:42,868
- She thinks it's from Hee Dong.
- "But that's from Hee Dong."

349
00:15:42,869 --> 00:15:43,929
Yes.

350
00:15:44,308 --> 00:15:46,208
But please don't be upset.

351
00:15:46,308 --> 00:15:47,577
I really want to get to know you.

352
00:15:47,578 --> 00:15:49,608
I even wrote you that letter yesterday.

353
00:15:51,078 --> 00:15:53,148
Oh, he told her!

354
00:15:53,948 --> 00:15:55,017
Letter?

355
00:15:55,018 --> 00:15:56,387
- She thought it was Hee Dong's.
- She thinks it's from Hee Dong.

356
00:15:56,388 --> 00:15:57,517
"But that's from Hee Dong."

357
00:15:57,518 --> 00:15:58,518
Yes.

358
00:16:00,458 --> 00:16:03,858
(Hoo wrote Si Woo a letter the night before.)

359
00:16:04,298 --> 00:16:06,297
(I know it's our second day, but we're only joking around...)

360
00:16:06,298 --> 00:16:08,197
(and scratching the surface.)

361
00:16:08,198 --> 00:16:10,068
(I'd like to get to know you better.)

362
00:16:11,068 --> 00:16:15,408
(Si Woo checked the letter this morning...)

363
00:16:16,638 --> 00:16:21,708
(and thought it was from Hee Dong.)

364
00:16:21,948 --> 00:16:23,248
Haven't you opened it yet?

365
00:16:23,548 --> 00:16:24,678
Wait, was that...

366
00:16:29,688 --> 00:16:30,688
(Grinning)

367
00:16:30,689 --> 00:16:32,157
- Who did you think it was?
- Was that you?

368
00:16:32,158 --> 00:16:33,818
- Who...
- The two-line letter.

369
00:16:34,928 --> 00:16:36,128
Who did you think it was from?

370
00:16:38,698 --> 00:16:41,428
I see. I understand now.

371
00:16:42,568 --> 00:16:45,768
It turns out that the letter wasn't from Hee Dong.

372
00:16:46,298 --> 00:16:48,538
It was from Hoo.

373
00:16:49,768 --> 00:16:52,038
I was ahead of myself.

374
00:16:52,138 --> 00:16:55,408
I knew it was too short.

375
00:16:55,678 --> 00:16:56,748
And...

376
00:16:57,648 --> 00:16:58,918
his words...

377
00:17:00,548 --> 00:17:02,888
sounded strange.

378
00:17:03,788 --> 00:17:05,387
I wasn't so sure about that letter.

379
00:17:05,388 --> 00:17:06,948
(Something felt off about this letter.)

380
00:17:07,058 --> 00:17:10,257
(The misunderstanding led to an awkward situation.)

381
00:17:10,258 --> 00:17:11,898
- She found out!
- The truth is revealed!

382
00:17:12,258 --> 00:17:13,997
- The truth has been revealed.
- Yes.

383
00:17:13,998 --> 00:17:16,728
She must feel good to know that it's from Hoo.

384
00:17:16,868 --> 00:17:18,737
It wasn't bad timing, son. It's fine.

385
00:17:18,738 --> 00:17:20,168
(It didn't end so poorly.)

386
00:17:21,408 --> 00:17:24,978
(They arrive at their first destination.)

387
00:17:25,538 --> 00:17:27,037
(A steakhouse recommended by Si Woo's dad)

388
00:17:27,038 --> 00:17:28,877
- A steakhouse.
- They're at a steakhouse.

389
00:17:28,878 --> 00:17:32,078
(What memory will they share here?)

390
00:17:32,378 --> 00:17:34,318
All right. You can sit here.

391
00:17:35,488 --> 00:17:38,387
(He hurries and gets the chair for her.)

392
00:17:38,388 --> 00:17:41,158
He never did that for Yu Bin.

393
00:17:41,728 --> 00:17:43,088
This is a nice view.

394
00:17:44,528 --> 00:17:45,628
- Do you agree?
- Yes.

395
00:17:46,858 --> 00:17:48,768
- It is.
- You're a bit cold, aren't you?

396
00:17:48,868 --> 00:17:50,198
Just a little.

397
00:17:50,898 --> 00:17:53,067
But it'll get in the way when I eat,

398
00:17:53,068 --> 00:17:54,428
- Sure.
- so I should take it off.

399
00:18:00,338 --> 00:18:05,378
(He naturally gets things for her.)

400
00:18:09,188 --> 00:18:11,188
- Oh, it's warm water.
- Is it?

401
00:18:12,718 --> 00:18:14,428
(Grinning)

402
00:18:18,758 --> 00:18:21,268
(Their food arrives.)

403
00:18:21,398 --> 00:18:22,398
Thank you.

404
00:18:22,728 --> 00:18:24,668
- It looks too big for you.
- It is.

405
00:18:25,038 --> 00:18:26,097
It's too much.

406
00:18:26,098 --> 00:18:30,268
(He gives her enough salad.)

407
00:18:31,608 --> 00:18:34,008
- She can't stop smiling.
- She looks happy.

408
00:18:35,108 --> 00:18:36,178
It looks delicious.

409
00:18:36,608 --> 00:18:37,977
(Their long-awaited steak arrives.)

410
00:18:37,978 --> 00:18:39,048
Thank you.

411
00:18:41,118 --> 00:18:43,148
(He takes his coat off...)

412
00:18:44,458 --> 00:18:47,288
(and stands up to cut the steak.)

413
00:18:48,188 --> 00:18:50,587
That doesn't seem so necessary.

414
00:18:50,588 --> 00:18:52,498
It is necessary.

415
00:18:53,628 --> 00:18:55,867
Hoo knows how to use his body.

416
00:18:55,868 --> 00:18:58,938
He knelt to dress a girl,

417
00:18:59,438 --> 00:19:00,897
- and now he's standing up...
- He's standing up...

418
00:19:00,898 --> 00:19:02,737
- to cut the steak.
- to cut the steak.

419
00:19:02,738 --> 00:19:04,777
It's not like a course meal from the chef.

420
00:19:04,778 --> 00:19:07,078
- Does he have to get up?
- I believe...

421
00:19:07,508 --> 00:19:09,648
it's a fundamental quality of a gentleman.

422
00:19:10,008 --> 00:19:11,817
Hoo majored in business, so...

423
00:19:11,818 --> 00:19:12,818
(Displeased)

424
00:19:15,148 --> 00:19:16,848
It's cooked very nicely.

425
00:19:17,118 --> 00:19:18,958
- Is it because it's medium?
- Yes.

426
00:19:20,118 --> 00:19:21,228
This is fat.

427
00:19:21,328 --> 00:19:23,658
(Only Si Woo's plate has pieces of steak.)

428
00:19:23,858 --> 00:19:26,018
You prefer cutting them all before eating them, right?

429
00:19:26,698 --> 00:19:27,698
Yes.

430
00:19:27,798 --> 00:19:29,798
- I prefer that, actually.
- You can stop, though.

431
00:19:30,568 --> 00:19:32,298
You should eat. I'll cut it up.

432
00:19:34,638 --> 00:19:38,508
(He finally has a bite.)

433
00:19:40,438 --> 00:19:41,478
It's good.

434
00:19:41,848 --> 00:19:43,348
(She finds him cute.)

435
00:19:45,278 --> 00:19:48,088
Have you talked to the guys a lot?

436
00:19:48,188 --> 00:19:49,718
- I have.
- Really?

437
00:19:50,748 --> 00:19:51,958
What did you talk about?

438
00:19:52,258 --> 00:19:53,418
About you.

439
00:19:56,128 --> 00:19:57,758
You were really popular.

440
00:19:57,958 --> 00:19:59,198
You talked about me?

441
00:20:00,058 --> 00:20:01,398
She's glad.

442
00:20:01,698 --> 00:20:02,768
Yes.

443
00:20:03,068 --> 00:20:05,508
I don't know about anything else, but you really are popular.

444
00:20:05,868 --> 00:20:07,398
And you're eating with her.

445
00:20:08,768 --> 00:20:10,737
- That was good.
- "And you're eating with her."

446
00:20:10,738 --> 00:20:12,278
(Impressed)

447
00:20:13,438 --> 00:20:14,958
I wish I could do more things for you.

448
00:20:15,278 --> 00:20:16,647
- Do you want some more?
- No.

449
00:20:16,648 --> 00:20:17,748
Take the whole plate.

450
00:20:18,218 --> 00:20:19,748
You have a way of framing people.

451
00:20:21,448 --> 00:20:22,588
Your responses...

452
00:20:23,548 --> 00:20:24,618
are cute.

453
00:20:25,388 --> 00:20:26,458
What was that?

454
00:20:28,258 --> 00:20:29,328
That was a good line.

455
00:20:29,758 --> 00:20:31,028
- Why did you laugh?
- No.

456
00:20:31,628 --> 00:20:33,158
You laughed too.

457
00:20:33,428 --> 00:20:35,727
I'm laughing because I'm happy...

458
00:20:35,728 --> 00:20:37,227
- about eating with a popular girl.
- I have a smiley face.

459
00:20:37,228 --> 00:20:38,338
- Do you?
- Yes.

460
00:20:39,498 --> 00:20:40,568
You're good at this.

461
00:20:41,338 --> 00:20:43,668
- They're joking around now.
- They seem closer now.

462
00:20:49,148 --> 00:20:50,248
It really is beautiful.

463
00:20:51,108 --> 00:20:53,148
I can't remember the last time I saw the landscape.

464
00:20:55,888 --> 00:20:56,948
It's pretty.

465
00:20:59,088 --> 00:21:00,187
Pretty.

466
00:21:00,188 --> 00:21:02,428
(Pretty.)

467
00:21:04,998 --> 00:21:06,027
Si Woo just...

468
00:21:06,028 --> 00:21:07,257
(Look at him go.)

469
00:21:07,258 --> 00:21:09,567
- Oh, my gosh.
- He's unstoppable!

470
00:21:09,568 --> 00:21:11,868
- Hoo was...
- Did he just call her beautiful?

471
00:21:12,268 --> 00:21:14,638
That punk!

472
00:21:16,068 --> 00:21:17,808
- He's practically flying.
- Hoo!

473
00:21:19,478 --> 00:21:20,778
I never knew he was like that.

474
00:21:21,278 --> 00:21:23,278
- Yu Bin is beautiful, - Okay.

475
00:21:23,378 --> 00:21:25,777
- and Si Woo is pretty.
- What's the difference?

476
00:21:25,778 --> 00:21:27,547
You should sue him.

477
00:21:27,548 --> 00:21:32,618
(Hoo is guilty of flirting.)

478
00:21:34,288 --> 00:21:37,858
You still want to go on a date with everyone, right?

479
00:21:38,458 --> 00:21:41,868
If I'm being honest, you were the one I wanted most.

480
00:21:42,168 --> 00:21:43,228
Because...

481
00:21:44,868 --> 00:21:46,567
As I said before,

482
00:21:46,568 --> 00:21:48,708
although it's not like we're running out of time,

483
00:21:48,838 --> 00:21:50,268
I don't know what will happen.

484
00:21:50,768 --> 00:21:52,008
I was...

485
00:21:52,778 --> 00:21:55,208
really curious about you too.

486
00:21:56,408 --> 00:21:57,847
So, thank you for that.

487
00:21:57,848 --> 00:22:01,118
(Hoo told her his honest feelings.)

488
00:22:01,948 --> 00:22:03,187
(Reaching)

489
00:22:03,188 --> 00:22:04,718
- What?
- Let's clink glasses.

490
00:22:05,088 --> 00:22:06,457
- With water?
- With water.

491
00:22:06,458 --> 00:22:11,528
(They feel much more comfortable now.)

492
00:22:16,168 --> 00:22:17,568
- Thank you for the meal.
- Thanks.

493
00:22:18,238 --> 00:22:21,537
Do you know how to wear a scarf?

494
00:22:21,538 --> 00:22:22,907
- A scarf? Do you want my help?
- Yes.

495
00:22:22,908 --> 00:22:25,677
- Yes, I don't know how.
- She wants him to help.

496
00:22:25,678 --> 00:22:27,207
- How did you do it before?
- Like...

497
00:22:27,208 --> 00:22:28,678
- Yu Bin helped me.
- I see.

498
00:22:29,178 --> 00:22:30,978
She did something.

499
00:22:31,278 --> 00:22:32,318
Like this.

500
00:22:37,288 --> 00:22:39,488
- Or should I put this in?
- Yes?

501
00:22:40,158 --> 00:22:41,957
Please see if it looks okay.

502
00:22:41,958 --> 00:22:43,528
He just gulped.

503
00:22:43,758 --> 00:22:44,828
Why did he gulp?

504
00:22:50,598 --> 00:22:51,668
Does it look similar?

505
00:22:52,098 --> 00:22:53,598
- It's perfect.
- Is it?

506
00:22:53,738 --> 00:22:54,738
Okay.

507
00:22:55,868 --> 00:22:57,808
- Shall we?
- Yes, you can go first.

508
00:22:58,208 --> 00:23:00,708
(He stays polite until the end.)

509
00:23:01,408 --> 00:23:02,908
Thank you for the food.

510
00:23:03,048 --> 00:23:04,717
- Thank you for the food.
- Thank you.

511
00:23:04,718 --> 00:23:06,078
- Goodbye.
- Bye.

512
00:23:06,878 --> 00:23:09,088
What was the point of acting like a married couple?

513
00:23:09,618 --> 00:23:11,817
How do you explain what happened...

514
00:23:11,818 --> 00:23:13,518
between Yu Bin and him?

515
00:23:14,288 --> 00:23:16,887
It's probably not what Yu Bin had in mind.

516
00:23:16,888 --> 00:23:18,557
- Definitely not.
- Exactly.

517
00:23:18,558 --> 00:23:20,757
Maybe it's because he's my son,

518
00:23:20,758 --> 00:23:23,168
but didn't he make her feel comfortable?

519
00:23:23,268 --> 00:23:24,327
- He did.
- I agree.

520
00:23:24,328 --> 00:23:25,697
- It was very smooth.
- Yes.

521
00:23:25,698 --> 00:23:27,837
- He's doing great.
- It was flawless.

522
00:23:27,838 --> 00:23:29,608
(Bitter for some reason)

523
00:23:31,268 --> 00:23:32,738
- Where are they?
- Who are they?

524
00:23:33,738 --> 00:23:36,708
(First-come First-served Date, Choi Yu Bin and You Hee Dong)

525
00:23:37,048 --> 00:23:39,218
(It's my daughter!)

526
00:23:39,318 --> 00:23:40,947
Yu Bin and Hee Dong should be fun to watch.

527
00:23:40,948 --> 00:23:43,148
I'm a little worried because Hee Dong is...

528
00:23:43,388 --> 00:23:45,188
too good-looking.

529
00:23:45,758 --> 00:23:47,888
Yu Bin is into good-looking men.

530
00:23:48,358 --> 00:23:50,087
- That's what worries me.
- So, my son is ugly?

531
00:23:50,088 --> 00:23:51,398
No, that's not...

532
00:23:52,058 --> 00:23:54,258
I can't say anything here.

533
00:23:55,028 --> 00:23:58,537
Yu Bin got to go on a date with Hee Dong, right?

534
00:23:58,538 --> 00:24:00,998
I believe that she may change her mind.

535
00:24:01,608 --> 00:24:04,407
What is going on?

536
00:24:04,408 --> 00:24:05,577
(The dads with sons have a war of nerves.)

537
00:24:05,578 --> 00:24:07,208
It's the Hee Dong magic.

538
00:24:11,378 --> 00:24:12,738
On a 1st-come, 1st-served basis...

539
00:24:12,778 --> 00:24:14,277
Did you know I'd pick you?

540
00:24:14,278 --> 00:24:16,347
No, I had no idea, even this time.

541
00:24:16,348 --> 00:24:17,418
Really?

542
00:24:18,488 --> 00:24:21,158
- We haven't talked...
- Right, we're not that close.

543
00:24:21,758 --> 00:24:23,258
I thought we were close.

544
00:24:24,588 --> 00:24:26,858
So did I.

545
00:24:26,998 --> 00:24:29,198
We're close,

546
00:24:29,228 --> 00:24:31,538
- but compared to others... Right?
- That's true.

547
00:24:32,938 --> 00:24:34,768
Who did you think I'd pick, then?

548
00:24:34,808 --> 00:24:37,268
I obviously thought you'd pick Hoo.

549
00:24:37,868 --> 00:24:39,437
(I see.)

550
00:24:39,438 --> 00:24:40,538
Right?

551
00:24:43,808 --> 00:24:45,377
But you did pick me, right?

552
00:24:45,378 --> 00:24:47,077
- Of course.
- Right?

553
00:24:47,078 --> 00:24:48,148
Of course, I did.

554
00:24:48,788 --> 00:24:52,558
- I've been waiting.
- Really?

555
00:24:52,988 --> 00:24:54,588
He says some great lines.

556
00:24:54,988 --> 00:24:57,757
- When I had that ten-minute chat...
- Yes.

557
00:24:57,758 --> 00:24:59,297
- with you, - Yes.

558
00:24:59,298 --> 00:25:01,667
I thought it was less awkward.

559
00:25:01,668 --> 00:25:02,668
(That's why I asked you out.)

560
00:25:02,669 --> 00:25:04,938
I thought our ten-minute chat yesterday...

561
00:25:05,568 --> 00:25:08,138
- went by pretty fast.
- So did I.

562
00:25:08,438 --> 00:25:11,678
I think we're on the same wavelength.

563
00:25:13,978 --> 00:25:15,048
He's glad.

564
00:25:16,278 --> 00:25:18,578
(Staring)

565
00:25:18,618 --> 00:25:20,177
Do you usually find it difficult...

566
00:25:20,178 --> 00:25:22,647
looking people in the eye when you have a conversation?

567
00:25:22,648 --> 00:25:23,648
That's right.

568
00:25:23,649 --> 00:25:26,487
I can't even look my friends in the eye.

569
00:25:26,488 --> 00:25:27,488
Seriously?

570
00:25:27,489 --> 00:25:29,687
Should we sit apart when we eat later?

571
00:25:29,688 --> 00:25:30,828
No, you don't have to.

572
00:25:33,158 --> 00:25:34,158
(Looking)

573
00:25:38,838 --> 00:25:41,807
(Look at these kids.)

574
00:25:41,808 --> 00:25:44,108
- It's going smoothly.
- Indeed.

575
00:25:44,808 --> 00:25:47,477
(A buffet recommended by Yu Bin's dad)

576
00:25:47,478 --> 00:25:48,547
It looks nice.

577
00:25:48,548 --> 00:25:52,048
(Yu Bin's dad picked the perfect spot for her.)

578
00:25:54,078 --> 00:25:55,287
That's a buffet? How nice.

579
00:25:55,288 --> 00:25:57,687
(Impressed)

580
00:25:57,688 --> 00:25:58,818
It's really pretty.

581
00:26:04,188 --> 00:26:07,357
(It's filled with flowers and makes you doubt it's actually a buffet.)

582
00:26:07,358 --> 00:26:09,098
- It looks like a wedding venue.
- It does.

583
00:26:09,498 --> 00:26:10,768
Not a buffet.

584
00:26:11,768 --> 00:26:14,238
They could have a wedding right there.

585
00:26:18,108 --> 00:26:19,277
I've never been to a place like this.

586
00:26:19,278 --> 00:26:20,508
- Really?
- Yes.

587
00:26:21,308 --> 00:26:25,048
It was so pretty and packed with flowers.

588
00:26:25,718 --> 00:26:27,778
I thought they'd serve a course meal,

589
00:26:28,178 --> 00:26:29,247
but it turned out to be a buffet.

590
00:26:29,248 --> 00:26:32,718
I thought my dad picked a spot that I would like.

591
00:26:34,488 --> 00:26:38,028
This place makes this feel like a blind date.

592
00:26:38,128 --> 00:26:39,427
- A blind date?
- The venue, I mean.

593
00:26:39,428 --> 00:26:40,958
- And there are two flowers.
- I know.

594
00:26:41,768 --> 00:26:43,968
I actually had them set it up.

595
00:26:44,568 --> 00:26:45,698
Amazing.

596
00:26:46,038 --> 00:26:48,167
You also told them to get ready to wrap these, right?

597
00:26:48,168 --> 00:26:50,267
- Obviously.
- Okay. You get a point.

598
00:26:50,268 --> 00:26:51,337
(They even share the same sense of humor.)

599
00:26:51,338 --> 00:26:52,378
Lovely.

600
00:26:52,978 --> 00:26:53,978
It's a buffet, so...

601
00:26:54,838 --> 00:26:56,408
- I think we can go.
- Should we go?

602
00:26:57,278 --> 00:27:00,377
(They go to get some food.)

603
00:27:00,378 --> 00:27:01,418
I'm excited.

604
00:27:01,748 --> 00:27:03,448
Yu Bin, don't bring too much food.

605
00:27:04,448 --> 00:27:05,688
You can finish all this, right?

606
00:27:05,918 --> 00:27:06,958
It's all ours.

607
00:27:07,588 --> 00:27:08,728
Okay.

608
00:27:09,428 --> 00:27:10,988
What do you usually go for at a buffet?

609
00:27:11,658 --> 00:27:13,857
I usually start with a salad...

610
00:27:13,858 --> 00:27:14,898
and get right to meat.

611
00:27:21,168 --> 00:27:25,208
(But...)

612
00:27:25,378 --> 00:27:27,107
That's an unbelievable amount for her.

613
00:27:27,108 --> 00:27:29,048
(She gets less food than expected.)

614
00:27:31,678 --> 00:27:34,417
- There's salad on her plate, right?
- Yes.

615
00:27:34,418 --> 00:27:36,594
She doesn't have any of the salads when we go together.

616
00:27:36,618 --> 00:27:39,288
This is very unfamiliar.

617
00:27:39,488 --> 00:27:42,028
She normally picks up the whole pot, right?

618
00:27:43,158 --> 00:27:44,188
Sit down.

619
00:27:44,928 --> 00:27:46,027
She's getting a small portion.

620
00:27:46,028 --> 00:27:47,028
(Scared)

621
00:27:50,468 --> 00:27:53,038
Is it okay to come to a buffet when it's our first date?

622
00:27:53,738 --> 00:27:55,868
- He must want you to eat up.
- Okay.

623
00:27:57,468 --> 00:27:58,708
(Poking)

624
00:28:00,278 --> 00:28:02,318
She brought salad, but she's eating the meat first.

625
00:28:06,878 --> 00:28:09,018
(Moaning)

626
00:28:10,948 --> 00:28:14,918
(She has a bite of cream pasta, her favorite.)

627
00:28:16,128 --> 00:28:17,188
- Is it good?
- Yes.

628
00:28:18,598 --> 00:28:20,758
Between this and the one you made, which is better?

629
00:28:22,228 --> 00:28:23,498
(Looking around)

630
00:28:24,098 --> 00:28:25,268
The one I made.

631
00:28:30,508 --> 00:28:34,438
I can be the judge only if I try your version.

632
00:28:35,078 --> 00:28:36,318
When do you want me to make it?

633
00:28:38,148 --> 00:28:39,448
- She's proactive.
- Clever.

634
00:28:39,518 --> 00:28:40,948
"When do you want me to make it?"

635
00:28:41,378 --> 00:28:43,887
- These kids...
- "These kids."

636
00:28:43,888 --> 00:28:46,288
I think she takes after her dad's gift of gab.

637
00:28:47,158 --> 00:28:48,398
When do you want me to make it?

638
00:28:49,988 --> 00:28:51,358
I'd eat it whenever.

639
00:28:53,528 --> 00:28:54,828
(Laughing)

640
00:28:55,028 --> 00:28:56,728
You can prep the ingredients next to me.

641
00:28:56,868 --> 00:28:57,868
Should I?

642
00:28:58,498 --> 00:29:01,668
(They make their own promise.)

643
00:29:04,938 --> 00:29:05,938
(Glancing)

644
00:29:10,778 --> 00:29:13,878
(She sets an appointment and properly starts eating.)

645
00:29:14,978 --> 00:29:15,988
(Glancing)

646
00:29:19,788 --> 00:29:22,428
(Staring)

647
00:29:24,988 --> 00:29:27,728
I thought it was nice that she felt comfortable enough...

648
00:29:27,898 --> 00:29:31,068
to eat a lot rather than being coy and eating little.

649
00:29:33,968 --> 00:29:35,068
You eat really well.

650
00:29:36,238 --> 00:29:37,668
(Stopping)

651
00:29:38,138 --> 00:29:40,608
It's a compliment. I like girls who eat well.

652
00:29:44,908 --> 00:29:46,018
You're very attentive.

653
00:29:48,278 --> 00:29:49,518
"Attentive?"

654
00:29:49,548 --> 00:29:51,648
I mean, you're thoughtful.

655
00:29:51,818 --> 00:29:52,917
That's my ideal type.

656
00:29:52,918 --> 00:29:54,058
- Really?
- Yes.

657
00:29:54,358 --> 00:29:55,598
Was I close to your ideal type?

658
00:29:55,928 --> 00:29:56,958
- Was I?
- Yes.

659
00:30:02,298 --> 00:30:03,628
Can you handle spicy food?

660
00:30:04,198 --> 00:30:05,298
(Scoffing)

661
00:30:05,938 --> 00:30:08,438
Didn't we talk about that in the living room?

662
00:30:09,338 --> 00:30:11,908
(In the evening on the first day)

663
00:30:12,038 --> 00:30:14,208
Carbonara Buldak is the spiciest I can handle.

664
00:30:14,738 --> 00:30:19,148
(She remembered his taste.)

665
00:30:19,378 --> 00:30:22,247
- You said, "Carbonara Buldak." - I did.

666
00:30:22,248 --> 00:30:23,594
(But Hee Dong doesn't remember what he said.)

667
00:30:23,618 --> 00:30:26,558
Things people say normally goes in one ear and out the other, right?

668
00:30:27,818 --> 00:30:28,828
No.

669
00:30:29,388 --> 00:30:33,928
My mind goes blank when I'm around a girl I like.

670
00:30:38,128 --> 00:30:39,467
(What was that line?)

671
00:30:39,468 --> 00:30:40,698
What was that?

672
00:30:41,098 --> 00:30:43,308
- What is with him?
- Tae Woong.

673
00:30:44,008 --> 00:30:45,968
Baseball wasn't the only thing he worked hard on.

674
00:30:46,108 --> 00:30:47,908
Is that what a kid should say?

675
00:30:48,338 --> 00:30:49,648
Is it?

676
00:30:49,948 --> 00:30:52,247
Baseball wasn't the only thing he practiced.

677
00:30:52,248 --> 00:30:53,577
He must have studied business as well.

678
00:30:53,578 --> 00:30:55,077
He said it so naturally.

679
00:30:55,078 --> 00:30:56,888
I think he has better lines than I do.

680
00:30:57,618 --> 00:31:00,317
I should go over my life again.

681
00:31:00,318 --> 00:31:01,717
I should hone my skills.

682
00:31:01,718 --> 00:31:03,027
I'm learning from him.

683
00:31:03,028 --> 00:31:04,268
I'll use that on my wife later.

684
00:31:07,758 --> 00:31:08,868
Did you enjoy it?

685
00:31:08,928 --> 00:31:09,928
- Yes.
- Good.

686
00:31:10,998 --> 00:31:12,038
Shall we go?

687
00:31:14,498 --> 00:31:15,708
For the photo.

688
00:31:15,808 --> 00:31:18,778
I'll get you some flowers next time when I get a chance.

689
00:31:19,178 --> 00:31:20,377
Do you want to take some?

690
00:31:20,378 --> 00:31:22,778
- You're tall enough to reach it.
- Of course.

691
00:31:23,548 --> 00:31:24,608
I'll take a rain check.

692
00:31:26,378 --> 00:31:27,948
It felt really new.

693
00:31:28,278 --> 00:31:31,987
At unexpected moments,

694
00:31:31,988 --> 00:31:33,488
Hee Dong...

695
00:31:34,058 --> 00:31:37,188
subtly flirted with me out of nowhere.

696
00:31:38,288 --> 00:31:41,728
So, it confused me.

697
00:31:43,628 --> 00:31:44,667
(Yu Bin is swaying after the date.)

698
00:31:44,668 --> 00:31:46,368
She remembers.

699
00:31:47,198 --> 00:31:48,198
- Hee Dong is pretty good.
- But...

700
00:31:48,199 --> 00:31:49,508
what about Hoo?

701
00:31:50,108 --> 00:31:52,437
Hee Dong looks like he's sitting still,

702
00:31:52,438 --> 00:31:54,477
but he's got some great lines.

703
00:31:54,478 --> 00:31:56,448
- He's a magician with words.
- He's a player.

704
00:31:56,478 --> 00:31:58,147
So, Hee Dong is also into her.

705
00:31:58,148 --> 00:31:59,378
He is.

706
00:31:59,978 --> 00:32:02,248
- It could be confusing.
- It could.

707
00:32:02,648 --> 00:32:04,387
They're giving each other some mixed signals.

708
00:32:04,388 --> 00:32:05,994
(What lies ahead for these two uncertain hearts?)

709
00:32:06,018 --> 00:32:07,387
(First-come First-served Date, Cho Eun Byul and Lee Jae Seung)

710
00:32:07,388 --> 00:32:08,788
She's having a date with Jae Seung.

711
00:32:09,328 --> 00:32:12,358
I hope things go well for Eun Byul and Jae Seung on this date.

712
00:32:15,698 --> 00:32:17,768
Who are you least close with?

713
00:32:18,498 --> 00:32:19,538
Is it me?

714
00:32:19,698 --> 00:32:21,068
Well...

715
00:32:21,768 --> 00:32:22,908
I see.

716
00:32:24,068 --> 00:32:26,437
- Who are you least close with?
- The one that just joined us.

717
00:32:26,438 --> 00:32:28,038
- Seo Yoon?
- Yes.

718
00:32:29,508 --> 00:32:31,548
- Am I next?
- No.

719
00:32:32,048 --> 00:32:34,218
I feel most comfortable...

720
00:32:34,848 --> 00:32:36,587
when I talk with you.

721
00:32:36,588 --> 00:32:37,617
- Really?
- Yes.

722
00:32:37,618 --> 00:32:38,888
I'm glad to hear that.

723
00:32:40,318 --> 00:32:44,757
Since we both talk softly, I find it comfortable.

724
00:32:44,758 --> 00:32:46,497
- Yes.
- They have the matching energy.

725
00:32:46,498 --> 00:32:47,998
They're off to a good start.

726
00:32:49,268 --> 00:32:50,767
Did you say you like to exercise?

727
00:32:50,768 --> 00:32:52,798
Yes, I like to exercise.

728
00:32:53,538 --> 00:32:54,768
Do you run too?

729
00:32:55,098 --> 00:32:56,338
Running...

730
00:32:57,208 --> 00:32:58,608
Just say you like it.

731
00:32:59,608 --> 00:33:00,708
My knees ache.

732
00:33:03,678 --> 00:33:05,048
"My knees ache."

733
00:33:05,448 --> 00:33:07,618
You should've just said yes.

734
00:33:07,978 --> 00:33:10,418
His knees already ache at that age?

735
00:33:10,518 --> 00:33:13,157
You're so young. Why would your knees ache?

736
00:33:13,158 --> 00:33:15,558
He should've been more witty about it.

737
00:33:15,658 --> 00:33:17,558
He speaks like an elderly.

738
00:33:17,688 --> 00:33:19,357
- Are his knees worn out already?
- Do you even know...

739
00:33:19,358 --> 00:33:20,478
what a knee ache feels like?

740
00:33:20,528 --> 00:33:21,928
What do I do with him?

741
00:33:22,868 --> 00:33:25,837
Your age is...

742
00:33:25,838 --> 00:33:26,968
No.

743
00:33:28,538 --> 00:33:30,108
Are you older than me?

744
00:33:31,238 --> 00:33:32,478
I might be.

745
00:33:33,438 --> 00:33:34,608
What about me?

746
00:33:35,038 --> 00:33:36,347
How old do I think you are?

747
00:33:36,348 --> 00:33:40,548
The way you speak is so mature and soft.

748
00:33:40,878 --> 00:33:43,288
So I think you're older than me.

749
00:33:44,188 --> 00:33:45,287
So I think you're older than me.

750
00:33:45,288 --> 00:33:46,488
- Really?
- Yes.

751
00:33:46,888 --> 00:33:50,158
(She forces a smile.)

752
00:33:50,228 --> 00:33:51,997
- This...
- Hey.

753
00:33:51,998 --> 00:33:54,197
- That was bad.
- They haven't revealed their ages.

754
00:33:54,198 --> 00:33:56,828
- They don't know.
- They've no information on that.

755
00:33:57,068 --> 00:33:59,538
Even if she's older than you, you shouldn't say that, punk.

756
00:34:00,598 --> 00:34:02,868
(The first date is a mess from the start.)

757
00:34:03,008 --> 00:34:05,208
He's innocent.

758
00:34:05,268 --> 00:34:07,738
- He's innocent.
- It's because he's innocent.

759
00:34:07,908 --> 00:34:09,878
Because his feelings are genuine.

760
00:34:10,708 --> 00:34:11,808
Older than him...

761
00:34:11,948 --> 00:34:15,887
No matter how genuine he is, there are things he shouldn't say.

762
00:34:15,888 --> 00:34:18,547
Telling a woman that she looks older than you...

763
00:34:18,548 --> 00:34:20,957
hurts her pride, you know?

764
00:34:20,958 --> 00:34:23,358
But he can't act all formal there.

765
00:34:23,528 --> 00:34:24,657
(Turning around)

766
00:34:24,658 --> 00:34:25,758
Who are you?

767
00:34:26,928 --> 00:34:29,097
Isn't it tough? This seems to be too much for you.

768
00:34:29,098 --> 00:34:31,898
Goodness. Jae Seung, get yourself together.

769
00:34:35,198 --> 00:34:38,808
When did you have your first relationship?

770
00:34:40,878 --> 00:34:44,108
I dated for two years back in high school.

771
00:34:44,708 --> 00:34:46,517
(Confessing his ex after confessing his knee pain)

772
00:34:46,518 --> 00:34:48,217
So...

773
00:34:48,218 --> 00:34:51,517
I grew a lot thanks to the girl I've dated for those two years.

774
00:34:51,518 --> 00:34:52,888
I became mature.

775
00:34:54,358 --> 00:34:56,458
She's my first love until now.

776
00:34:56,888 --> 00:34:58,358
Why is he saying all that?

777
00:34:58,658 --> 00:35:00,528
Dating for two years in high school...

778
00:35:00,658 --> 00:35:02,568
- He's sharing too much.
- Yes.

779
00:35:02,668 --> 00:35:03,998
That's understandable.

780
00:35:04,868 --> 00:35:06,698
Did you have post-breakup syndrome?

781
00:35:08,368 --> 00:35:10,868
(The topic took a deep turn.)

782
00:35:10,908 --> 00:35:13,537
People say your heart aches...

783
00:35:13,538 --> 00:35:15,878
- when you break up.
- Yes.

784
00:35:15,908 --> 00:35:19,117
It's not just figurative.

785
00:35:19,118 --> 00:35:21,648
It really hurts.

786
00:35:22,888 --> 00:35:23,987
Did you never feel it?

787
00:35:23,988 --> 00:35:25,618
- Well...
- I'm serious.

788
00:35:25,858 --> 00:35:27,118
I mean it.

789
00:35:27,218 --> 00:35:28,987
- I know what it is.
- You do?

790
00:35:28,988 --> 00:35:31,928
It feels like there's a rock placed on me.

791
00:35:33,358 --> 00:35:34,857
- Yes.
- I'm serious.

792
00:35:34,858 --> 00:35:36,068
I know.

793
00:35:36,198 --> 00:35:37,767
- I can really relate.
- You know how it feels?

794
00:35:37,768 --> 00:35:38,968
- Yes.
- I'm glad.

795
00:35:39,368 --> 00:35:41,267
(She tries her best to relate.)

796
00:35:41,268 --> 00:35:42,368
I see.

797
00:35:42,668 --> 00:35:44,067
My goodness.

798
00:35:44,068 --> 00:35:46,077
He has zero talent...

799
00:35:46,078 --> 00:35:48,078
- in dating.
- Don't do that.

800
00:35:48,308 --> 00:35:49,347
It hasn't been long since he broke up,

801
00:35:49,348 --> 00:35:51,208
but why is he bringing it up now?

802
00:35:51,678 --> 00:35:54,678
- About his first love...
- Eun Byul didn't even ask,

803
00:35:54,878 --> 00:35:56,787
so did he need...

804
00:35:56,788 --> 00:35:59,188
to say it voluntarily, and in that situation too?

805
00:35:59,758 --> 00:36:03,557
It's not a counseling session.

806
00:36:03,558 --> 00:36:06,758
He feels awkward and so on, so he went and talked about himself,

807
00:36:06,958 --> 00:36:08,097
but he chose the wrong topic.

808
00:36:08,098 --> 00:36:10,128
- Yes.
- Why'd he mention his first love?

809
00:36:10,368 --> 00:36:13,067
But on the other hand, compared to the guy who goes to any woman...

810
00:36:13,068 --> 00:36:16,308
and says she's pretty and beautiful,

811
00:36:16,468 --> 00:36:17,807
- it might be better...
- He's much better, right?

812
00:36:17,808 --> 00:36:19,137
- to be innocent...
- Right?

813
00:36:19,138 --> 00:36:20,814
- and share about himself.
- You understand.

814
00:36:20,838 --> 00:36:22,007
- Yes.
- "You're pretty like an ice queen."

815
00:36:22,008 --> 00:36:23,047
It's better than saying pretty to this girl...

816
00:36:23,048 --> 00:36:24,477
- and beautiful to another girl.
- It's better than empty words.

817
00:36:24,478 --> 00:36:26,277
- He's sharing his first love story.
- Yes.

818
00:36:26,278 --> 00:36:27,717
- It means he's sincere.
- Exactly.

819
00:36:27,718 --> 00:36:29,948
I think my son is very innocent.

820
00:36:30,488 --> 00:36:31,647
He says what he thinks.

821
00:36:31,648 --> 00:36:33,017
- Which son is innocent now?
- "You're pretty."

822
00:36:33,018 --> 00:36:35,088
- "You're beautiful." - Which son?

823
00:36:36,658 --> 00:36:40,598
(After a lot of twists and turns, they arrive at...)

824
00:36:41,698 --> 00:36:43,127
(An arcade recommended by Eun Byul's mom)

825
00:36:43,128 --> 00:36:44,898
- They're at an arcade.
- They've arrived.

826
00:36:50,668 --> 00:36:53,537
- Your mother must like it.
- "Your mother must like it."

827
00:36:53,538 --> 00:36:55,508
Yes, I really like arcades.

828
00:36:55,848 --> 00:36:56,848
My gosh.

829
00:36:57,748 --> 00:36:59,124
- It's so...
- Which game do you like?

830
00:36:59,148 --> 00:37:00,348
- Me?
- Yes.

831
00:37:00,618 --> 00:37:02,187
- Basketball.
- Basketball? Shall we play it?

832
00:37:02,188 --> 00:37:03,217
The basketball game.

833
00:37:03,218 --> 00:37:04,348
Are you confident?

834
00:37:04,648 --> 00:37:05,658
Very.

835
00:37:05,818 --> 00:37:07,018
It's fine if you lose, right?

836
00:37:08,758 --> 00:37:10,188
I'm very good at it.

837
00:37:11,558 --> 00:37:14,697
(The basketball game starts.)

838
00:37:14,698 --> 00:37:15,728
Who'll win?

839
00:37:20,098 --> 00:37:23,308
(Unlike what he said, Jae Seung's balls keep missing the hoop.)

840
00:37:23,408 --> 00:37:26,577
(On the other hand, Eun Byul has a very steady posture.)

841
00:37:26,578 --> 00:37:27,977
- Eun Byul must've done it often.
- Eun Byul is good at it...

842
00:37:27,978 --> 00:37:29,678
because she's played it many times.

843
00:37:29,948 --> 00:37:31,348
She's played it a lot.

844
00:37:33,718 --> 00:37:35,018
Eun Byul is much better.

845
00:37:35,318 --> 00:37:36,818
She's good.

846
00:37:36,888 --> 00:37:38,448
The score difference is big.

847
00:37:38,488 --> 00:37:41,418
Eun Byul's wrist snap and posture...

848
00:37:41,518 --> 00:37:42,788
look like that of a pro.

849
00:37:45,528 --> 00:37:47,828
(But Jae Seung has almost caught up.)

850
00:37:49,728 --> 00:37:51,467
- Yes, lose to her.
- No.

851
00:37:51,468 --> 00:37:52,537
He should lose, right?

852
00:37:52,538 --> 00:37:53,867
He should. What good comes out of him winning?

853
00:37:53,868 --> 00:37:55,268
He shouldn't win.

854
00:37:59,408 --> 00:38:04,447
Actually, I thought I'd look cool if I played basketball well,

855
00:38:04,448 --> 00:38:06,418
so I clenched my teeth and gave it my all.

856
00:38:09,618 --> 00:38:13,258
(Meanwhile, Eun Byul runs out of stamina and starts to slow down.)

857
00:38:15,728 --> 00:38:18,788
(Final score: Eun Byul, 127)

858
00:38:21,328 --> 00:38:22,428
No.

859
00:38:23,428 --> 00:38:25,188
(Final score, Eun Byul: 127, Jae Seung: 133)

860
00:38:25,268 --> 00:38:27,297
(With a bright smile, )

861
00:38:27,298 --> 00:38:29,438
(Jae Seung wins.)

862
00:38:29,608 --> 00:38:31,408
What? It's a draw...

863
00:38:31,438 --> 00:38:32,438
No.

864
00:38:32,708 --> 00:38:34,177
He overtakes her.

865
00:38:34,178 --> 00:38:35,677
Good job.

866
00:38:35,678 --> 00:38:37,348
- He won in the end.
- Jae Seung.

867
00:38:37,648 --> 00:38:39,647
He tried so hard to beat her.

868
00:38:39,648 --> 00:38:41,177
- Why would he win?
- Anyway...

869
00:38:41,178 --> 00:38:43,048
He shouldn't have won.

870
00:38:43,518 --> 00:38:44,917
- He should've lost.
- He needs to lose.

871
00:38:44,918 --> 00:38:46,887
He's so slow.

872
00:38:46,888 --> 00:38:48,717
Like father, like son.

873
00:38:48,718 --> 00:38:51,128
Jae Seung's family seems to be very innocent.

874
00:38:51,758 --> 00:38:55,158
- He should've lost.
- He should've let her win.

875
00:38:57,128 --> 00:38:59,298
It was so close.

876
00:38:59,668 --> 00:39:02,137
- Just now, - You're so good.

877
00:39:02,138 --> 00:39:03,368
It was a draw.

878
00:39:04,738 --> 00:39:06,078
I think that made the game...

879
00:39:06,838 --> 00:39:08,038
a lot fiercer.

880
00:39:09,478 --> 00:39:11,777
(Do you think winning the basketball game...)

881
00:39:11,778 --> 00:39:13,447
(appealed to Eun Byul?)

882
00:39:13,448 --> 00:39:15,888
I don't think so. Eun Byul...

883
00:39:16,088 --> 00:39:18,818
was very upset because she lost to me.

884
00:39:21,358 --> 00:39:23,988
(Wailing)

885
00:39:24,028 --> 00:39:26,327
(The atmosphere here is like a funeral home.)

886
00:39:26,328 --> 00:39:28,997
It becomes a problem when he's good at something too.

887
00:39:28,998 --> 00:39:30,527
Did you have to win that game?

888
00:39:30,528 --> 00:39:31,868
You knew.

889
00:39:31,898 --> 00:39:34,597
Things seem to work out, but it doesn't.

890
00:39:34,598 --> 00:39:36,007
- There's something...
- It's a shame.

891
00:39:36,008 --> 00:39:37,107
I'm so frustrated.

892
00:39:37,108 --> 00:39:38,968
There's always something lacking.

893
00:39:39,978 --> 00:39:41,407
- Shall we get going?
- Sure.

894
00:39:41,408 --> 00:39:42,478
Okay.

895
00:39:42,508 --> 00:39:44,547
The son and daughter of national athletes.

896
00:39:44,548 --> 00:39:46,778
- You're right.
- You're right.

897
00:39:52,858 --> 00:39:54,764
You haven't cracked open the fortune cookie yet, have you?

898
00:39:54,788 --> 00:39:56,787
I cracked the fortune cookie.

899
00:39:56,788 --> 00:39:58,357
- You did?
- Yes, I did.

900
00:39:58,358 --> 00:39:59,358
Really?

901
00:39:59,359 --> 00:40:01,097
I was surprised that you came to me.

902
00:40:01,098 --> 00:40:02,428
- Really?
- Yes.

903
00:40:02,628 --> 00:40:04,768
- Did you come to me first?
- Why? Yes.

904
00:40:04,898 --> 00:40:06,198
- Really?
- Yes.

905
00:40:07,538 --> 00:40:08,798
Really? Thank you.

906
00:40:09,738 --> 00:40:10,767
You're welcome.

907
00:40:10,768 --> 00:40:12,437
(Feeling shy)

908
00:40:12,438 --> 00:40:14,138
I didn't think you'd come to me.

909
00:40:14,408 --> 00:40:16,378
I honestly had no idea whom you'd choose.

910
00:40:18,478 --> 00:40:21,418
But I really liked our talk yesterday.

911
00:40:21,518 --> 00:40:22,718
- Me too.
- Yes.

912
00:40:27,858 --> 00:40:30,288
- Let's talk more today.
- I'd like that.

913
00:40:30,788 --> 00:40:33,528
It'll be fun. Although I don't know what we'll be doing.

914
00:40:35,258 --> 00:40:37,467
You seem like the playful type.

915
00:40:37,468 --> 00:40:38,528
Yes.

916
00:40:38,768 --> 00:40:40,538
I have a feeling we'll hit it off.

917
00:40:40,738 --> 00:40:43,108
Our preferences are similar.

918
00:40:43,308 --> 00:40:45,367
Hold on, isn't he flirting?

919
00:40:45,368 --> 00:40:46,784
(The atmosphere is pleasant from the beginning.)

920
00:40:46,808 --> 00:40:49,308
- Do you go to cafes often?
- Yes.

921
00:40:50,008 --> 00:40:51,607
- As in, do I like them?
- Yes.

922
00:40:51,608 --> 00:40:54,418
I don't really drink coffee.

923
00:40:55,048 --> 00:40:56,347
- Me either.
- Really?

924
00:40:56,348 --> 00:40:57,788
What do you drink often?

925
00:40:57,988 --> 00:40:59,457
- I drink water.
- Water.

926
00:40:59,458 --> 00:41:01,258
I drink water like I'm a hippo.

927
00:41:01,388 --> 00:41:03,557
- I really like drinking water too.
- Really?

928
00:41:03,558 --> 00:41:05,357
I really liked science.

929
00:41:05,358 --> 00:41:06,897
I really like science too.

930
00:41:06,898 --> 00:41:09,567
I really liked body, physique, cells, and so on.

931
00:41:09,568 --> 00:41:11,327
I wanted to major in that.

932
00:41:11,328 --> 00:41:12,498
- Really?
- Yes.

933
00:41:12,668 --> 00:41:14,197
We have a lot in common.

934
00:41:14,198 --> 00:41:16,038
- I think so.
- Yes.

935
00:41:16,208 --> 00:41:18,667
You like going to vacation spots, you said.

936
00:41:18,668 --> 00:41:20,838
Yes, I go walk around,

937
00:41:21,108 --> 00:41:22,238
swim,

938
00:41:22,678 --> 00:41:24,307
take a boat...

939
00:41:24,308 --> 00:41:26,248
to go snorkeling and so on.

940
00:41:26,448 --> 00:41:27,847
I totally like stuff like that too.

941
00:41:27,848 --> 00:41:28,948
- Really?
- Yes.

942
00:41:29,548 --> 00:41:31,318
They have a lot in common.

943
00:41:31,918 --> 00:41:33,757
Everything they say...

944
00:41:33,758 --> 00:41:35,218
- is a common ground.
- Exactly.

945
00:41:35,388 --> 00:41:36,527
When he was with Eun Byul,

946
00:41:36,528 --> 00:41:39,104
- they had a lot in common too.
- He caters to everything she says.

947
00:41:39,128 --> 00:41:41,658
(The date with Eun Byul the day before)

948
00:41:41,798 --> 00:41:44,497
I'm sad that I'm allergic to cat fur.

949
00:41:44,498 --> 00:41:47,498
(He had a lot in common with Eun Byul too.)

950
00:41:48,398 --> 00:41:50,007
We have a lot in common.

951
00:41:50,008 --> 00:41:51,737
- I think so.
- Yes.

952
00:41:51,738 --> 00:41:53,577
Is it possible to have so many things in common...

953
00:41:53,578 --> 00:41:54,638
with every girl he meets?

954
00:41:54,838 --> 00:41:56,378
I know, right? It's fascinating.

955
00:41:57,048 --> 00:42:00,047
He just flip-flops, doesn't he?

956
00:42:00,048 --> 00:42:01,378
- That's right.
- Does he?

957
00:42:01,718 --> 00:42:04,947
Jae Hyuk does like all those things.

958
00:42:04,948 --> 00:42:06,918
So he's just expressing himself.

959
00:42:08,658 --> 00:42:12,258
I'm the type to have a long situationship.

960
00:42:13,358 --> 00:42:14,457
I think I'm like that too.

961
00:42:14,458 --> 00:42:15,727
- Really?
- Yes.

962
00:42:15,728 --> 00:42:18,098
Do you express your feelings first?

963
00:42:18,228 --> 00:42:19,598
- I do, - Yes.

964
00:42:19,968 --> 00:42:22,338
But if it seems like the feelings aren't mutual,

965
00:42:22,938 --> 00:42:24,138
I stop.

966
00:42:24,538 --> 00:42:26,538
They might find it uncomfortable.

967
00:42:27,208 --> 00:42:28,407
You're just like me.

968
00:42:28,408 --> 00:42:30,677
- Really?
- Yes, that's exactly what I do.

969
00:42:30,678 --> 00:42:31,777
- Seriously?
- Yes.

970
00:42:31,778 --> 00:42:32,818
Are you...

971
00:42:34,278 --> 00:42:35,818
my twin?

972
00:42:38,018 --> 00:42:40,117
Who is your father?

973
00:42:40,118 --> 00:42:42,388
I'm Woo Jae Hyuk.

974
00:42:47,058 --> 00:42:49,197
- "I'm Woo Jae Hyuk." - "I'm Woo Jae Hyuk."

975
00:42:49,198 --> 00:42:50,728
What's with Woo Jae Hyuk?

976
00:42:51,668 --> 00:42:53,537
He's witty.

977
00:42:53,538 --> 00:42:54,738
He changed his surname.

978
00:42:55,438 --> 00:42:56,667
I'm Woo Jae Hyuk.

979
00:42:56,668 --> 00:42:59,137
(Shin Jae Hyuk, Shin Tae Yong's son)

980
00:42:59,138 --> 00:43:00,407
I'm Shin Seo Yoon.

981
00:43:00,408 --> 00:43:02,438
(Woo Seo Yoon, Woo Ji Won's daughter)

982
00:43:03,878 --> 00:43:05,648
He was really like my twin.

983
00:43:05,878 --> 00:43:09,288
Our preferences, personalities,

984
00:43:09,518 --> 00:43:13,088
and behaviors were so similar.

985
00:43:13,558 --> 00:43:16,587
We kept the conversation going...

986
00:43:16,588 --> 00:43:18,958
and really had a proper talk.

987
00:43:20,098 --> 00:43:23,168
I've never met someone who's so similar to me.

988
00:43:23,568 --> 00:43:26,538
We ended up talking about dating along the way.

989
00:43:26,838 --> 00:43:29,568
And we had similar values regarding it too.

990
00:43:29,968 --> 00:43:31,108
I was surprised.

991
00:43:31,768 --> 00:43:34,178
You had similar values with Eun Byul too.

992
00:43:34,778 --> 00:43:36,578
(Feeling awkward)

993
00:43:38,378 --> 00:43:40,647
- That didn't take long.
- Right.

994
00:43:40,648 --> 00:43:42,178
- That was fast.
- Yes.

995
00:43:42,418 --> 00:43:43,988
I didn't expect to arrive so soon.

996
00:43:44,418 --> 00:43:45,888
- As we talked, - Exactly.

997
00:43:46,118 --> 00:43:47,258
Time flew.

998
00:43:47,388 --> 00:43:48,718
Time passed so fast.

999
00:43:49,888 --> 00:43:51,357
What a shame.

1000
00:43:51,358 --> 00:43:53,858
(What a shame.)

1001
00:43:56,728 --> 00:43:58,744
I'd like to spend more time, so should I slow down?

1002
00:43:58,768 --> 00:43:59,838
Sure.

1003
00:44:01,468 --> 00:44:06,538
(They got a lot closer from talking.)

1004
00:44:07,478 --> 00:44:09,008
- We must be here.
- Yes, we're here.

1005
00:44:10,148 --> 00:44:11,608
- That was so fast.
- I know.

1006
00:44:12,718 --> 00:44:15,918
I think I can park here.

1007
00:44:16,188 --> 00:44:17,847
(Hot spring, 800m)

1008
00:44:17,848 --> 00:44:20,418
(Seo Yoon spots the sign.)

1009
00:44:22,518 --> 00:44:25,288
It was an outdoor pool.

1010
00:44:25,998 --> 00:44:27,758
I was very surprised.

1011
00:44:29,368 --> 00:44:33,298
I'd never have imagined it as the first date location.

1012
00:44:33,668 --> 00:44:35,437
Seo Yoon, your father planned it.

1013
00:44:35,438 --> 00:44:37,938
- I planned it. Sorry.
- Your dad planned it.

1014
00:44:39,168 --> 00:44:41,177
(Another person who's worried)

1015
00:44:41,178 --> 00:44:42,708
I thought, "This is bad."

1016
00:44:43,278 --> 00:44:44,678
In my head,

1017
00:44:47,018 --> 00:44:49,388
I was thinking that I needed time to pump my muscles.

1018
00:44:50,148 --> 00:44:51,987
- That's right.
- Pumping his muscles.

1019
00:44:51,988 --> 00:44:53,717
- That's right.
- He must pump them.

1020
00:44:53,718 --> 00:44:55,999
Since he's showing them, might as well show off properly.

1021
00:44:56,528 --> 00:45:01,598
(A hot spring pool recommended by Woo Seo Yoon's dad)

1022
00:45:02,698 --> 00:45:04,398
- Shall we go outside?
- Let's go.

1023
00:45:06,498 --> 00:45:07,638
- Thank you.
- No problem.

1024
00:45:11,108 --> 00:45:12,168
It's nice.

1025
00:45:13,478 --> 00:45:16,177
It's cold, but the water looks warm.

1026
00:45:16,178 --> 00:45:18,508
- It's nice.
- Yes. And it's so big.

1027
00:45:19,548 --> 00:45:21,418
- Shall we place our clothes here?
- Yes.

1028
00:45:22,078 --> 00:45:23,247
- Is here fine?
- Sure.

1029
00:45:23,248 --> 00:45:25,717
(It's time to show off his pumped muscles.)

1030
00:45:25,718 --> 00:45:26,888
It's going to be cold.

1031
00:45:28,418 --> 00:45:29,758
Here it comes.

1032
00:45:33,458 --> 00:45:34,527
- Jae Hyuk.
- Jae Hyuk.

1033
00:45:34,528 --> 00:45:35,798
(He looks incredible!)

1034
00:45:38,528 --> 00:45:40,798
Is this "Single's Inferno?"

1035
00:45:42,498 --> 00:45:44,267
He's so cool.

1036
00:45:44,268 --> 00:45:46,478
(Boldly taking off his top)

1037
00:45:46,808 --> 00:45:48,107
(His dad is satisfied.)

1038
00:45:48,108 --> 00:45:49,208
Nice.

1039
00:45:49,678 --> 00:45:52,508
(Seo Yoon's dad is satisfied too.)

1040
00:45:52,948 --> 00:45:56,218
(Meanwhile, Seo Yoon...)

1041
00:45:57,018 --> 00:45:58,548
You must be so cold.

1042
00:45:58,788 --> 00:46:00,557
Shall we enter the water quickly? It's cold.

1043
00:46:00,558 --> 00:46:01,758
- Let's go in.
- Yes.

1044
00:46:02,418 --> 00:46:04,758
I felt so shy.

1045
